      "instruction": "<p>Deseed your<strong> peppers</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into rough, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped peppers</strong> and cook for 4-5 min, turning occasionally, until starting to char and soften – these are your <strong>charred peppers</strong></p>",
